# RUN.md — [VARIABLE: PROJECT_NAME]

Autonomous run entry for this workspace. Only present if `autonomous_level` was `autonomous` at launch.

---

## Prerequisites

- Workspace composed by `project-launcher`
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in environment
- Archon available at `C:/Users/robin/Downloads/Archon` (or equivalent)

---

## Single-command autonomous build

```bash
cd "[VARIABLE: TARGET_PATH]"

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY" \
  bun run --cwd "C:/Users/robin/Downloads/Archon" cli workflow run autonomous-build \
  --cwd "[VARIABLE: TARGET_PATH]" \
  --no-worktree
```

The workflow reads `.archon/workflows/autonomous-build.yaml` in this workspace and executes each phase as a DAG node with verification between.

---

## Monitoring

The agent writes progress to:

- `docs/sessions/session-*.md` — per-session summaries
- `docs/discoveries.md` — learnings
- `docs/showcases/` — phase audits

Tail the most recent session file to follow along.

---

## On completion

When the final phase passes:

1. Check `docs/showcases/final-showcase.md` for the final audit
2. Review any `[BROKEN]` or `[INCOMPLETE]` badges — these are real issues
3. If all green, the project is ready to ship

---

## On stuck

Agent writes to `docs/questions.md` when it hits a decision it can't make autonomously. Check this file first if the run seems stalled.

If truly stuck (agent crashed or exceeded budget), restart from the last passing phase:

```bash
# Find last passing verify
ls -t verify/phase-*.sh | head -1

# Resume from the next phase manually
```
